	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I already mentioned it somewhere in the thread, there is yet another use for extended NROM besides homebrews and FDS hacks - hacks of popular NROM games such as Battle City. In fact, author of the <a href="http://www.romhacking.net/hacks/569/" class="postlink">Binary City</a> optimized some code to get extra room for new features, and stopped to add stuff into the game when he ran out of room completely. With extended NROM such project would have a chance to be made faster and be even larger.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
