	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't want to complain too much, but using a sub mapper makes sense to me.  I thought that was part of the point of them, to prevent these cases where multiple mappers are lumped together as a single "mapper number", then you have to do hacky things to detect which type it is.
<br />
<br />Not that it wouldn't work, or be any less usable, just seems like an unnecessary hack to use the ROM size instead of the mapper descriptor to describe the mapper.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


