<br />
<br />That's true, but I would think that emulators would always treat a ROM as being mirrored (up to the max size supported by the board, which may be larger than the ROM used).  Because it will do that anyways, I would think emulators wouldn't need to know the difference betwen NROM-128 and NROM-256.

		

